description:
The issue kicks off in the Hellhouse. Zoe is there, continuing to keep tabs on Mary so she doesn't mess with Deadpool. To further her goal, Zoe wants LL & L to prep a bodyslide for the last known location of Siryn, hoping she'll find Deadpool there.

Meanwhile, Deadpool is combing the countryside with his buddy Weasel, looking for Siryn (who is in the midwest with X-Force). They don't find her. They do find T-Ray and he's angry. They prepare to battle, but Zoe appears and tells him not to fight with T-Ray because he will lose, for it will push him over the edge mentally (he's been under a lot fo strain recently). Deadpool argues that he is fine and T-Ray is his problem, not hers . He decides to leave with her anyway because she may know where Siryn is.

After a talk with Al, Deadpool smells a foreign scent in his headquarters (which is strictly forbidden). He goes ballistic. Al calms him down with a slap to the face. He leaves to go find Siryn.

He finds her and Warpath (who's not too fond of Deadpool) at the Field of Dreams ballpark. Warpath is very combative. They get into a fight, which doesn't please Siryn. She asks him to leave. He tries to explain, but she won't listen. Remembering how Al slapping him made him think clearer, he almost slaps Siryn but doesn't. She storms off.

Deadpool returns to the basball field later that night, drunk and depressed. Siryn returns and confesses that she also needs and loves him. The issue ends with Deadpool getting all around the bases while staying on home base.

List of covers and their creators:

CoverNameCreator(s)Sidebar Location
RegRegular CoverNathan Massengill & Pete Woods1
VarDC Head Spoof CoverNathan Massengill & Pete Woods2
name: Drowning Man Part 1 or Things to Do in Iowa When You're Deadpool

description:
First Appearance of Cameron Chase! When the Clayfaces create a new, eerie version of themselves, Batman joins forces with Chase, a detective who specializes in hunting paranormals. It's an uneasy partnership at best, which may give the Clayfaces the edge they need.

A scientist studying Clayface (05 - Cassius) was attacked by a "sample" taken from the child. The doctor was overtaken by the clay entity, giving him the ability to melt things from a distance. It headed toward Gotham City to find its parents. D.E.O. (Department of Extra-normal Operations) agent Cameron Chase was assigned to "Clay-Thing." Batman got to her at the cave where he was born and learned what she knew. They confronted it at Arkham Asylum. Clay-Thing liquidized before them.

(Includes bound-in, perforated D.E.O. file card sheet featuring Cameron Chase, Batman, Claything and Catwoman.)
name: Chasing Clay

description:
Obsession has a crush on Superman that borders on stalking. But now there are two Supermen…does that mean there's twice as much for Obsession to love? Not if Maxima has anything to say about it! Can the Supermen survive all this affection?

Superman is split into two personalities: red and blue. They are facing domestic problems with Lois. So the two of them plan to go to The Fortress of Solitude to find a way to merge together.

Upon arriving at the Fortress, they are greeted by Dana Dearden, a.k.a. Obsession. She loves having two Supermen around her. But her joys are short-lived. Maxima arrives a brief while later to lay claim on the Supermen.

Dana is reluctant to part with her beloved and engages Maxima in a battle. They are almost on the verge of ruining the Fortress, when Superman red pushes them outside. Then the two Supermen arrive in a mecha-suit. This distracts Dana and Maxima uses it to her advantage to implant the thought of Superman dying in Dana's mind. Dana is unable to take it and flees.

Superman blue then plants a device on Maxima's head to prevent her from accessing her powers. She is then taken to Belle Reve to have her contained. Maxima says that the next time they meet, she will declare war on Superman.
name: Who Do You Love?

description: Mike LeRoi and Detective DeFilo head for a vacation in Florida, but getting away from New Orleans doesn't mean getting away from the dark forces that call the Big Easy home! Will the vodoun killers of the Societé manage to kill the two of them, or just their relationship?
name: Clear Blue Skies, Part 1

description:
PKNA #13

La notte più buia / The Darkest Night
name: La notte più buia

description: Dougie and Ivor wide up trying to sell their fake cocaine to Mr. Bell who was the original owner of the product. As a result multiple attempts are made on both Ivor and Dougie's lives in very quick succession. Mr. Bell and his men meet in the three way dual with Dougie's Father in Law and The Zombie of Uncle Shuggie which culminates into a huge blood bath as Dougie and Ivor manage to out wit and kill them all.
Luse faces off with Jace and Morachi and Talon discuss  Sanctuaries next move.
name: Six: Big Payback

story_arc_credits.name: Sanctuary Book 5: The Wolf One: Freedoms Just Another Word For Nothing Left To Lose

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: Sanctuary Book 5: The Wolf One: Freedoms Just Another Word For Nothing Left To Lose

description: The Bones flee the enraged Roque Ja and escape into a tunnel in the mountainside. On the other side they discover a magnificent abandoned temple to the Dragons, and wonder about Roque Ja's tale that the mountains themselves were created long ago when the Dragons fought and pushed up the land. As the Bones try to make their way back towards the valley, they encounter the two Rat Creatures, but before they can give chase, Kingdok appears. He is angry at the two Rat Creatures for deserting him, and attacks them and the Bones.
name: Rat Creature Temple

description: Green Lantern heads to Hawaii to help the Teen of Steel against an out of control goddess. Story continues in Superboy (1994 3rd Series) #47.
name: Idol Worship Part 1: Sacrificial Lambs!

description: Boy storms an American death camp in search of her brother while The Invisibles try to save her from the evils of the Hand of Glory, which could potentially open the doorway to a dimension of terror. Meanwhile, the ultimate assassin prepares to hunt down King Mob.
name: Counting to Five
Slave of Heavens, Prologue: The End

description:
Ogun has infiltrated the computers of the S.H.I.E.L.D. Helicarrier, and manipulated the agency into bringing Kitty Pryde aboard to tackle the computer problems. While dealing with Ogun, Kitty and her ally, Rigby Fallon discover her missing dragon, Lockheed, has stowed away inside her baggage.

Meanwhile, Wolverine, having been lured toward the Helicarrier by Ogun, reaches the rendezvous point on the Brooklyn Bridge where he expects to meet Kitty. He jumps his motorcycle from the bridge onto the Helicarrier which Ogun has careening recklessly through and around New York City.

Kitty manages to shut down the computers, allowing Dum Dum Dugan to assume manual control of the aircraft, just as Wolverine makes his way into the computer room. Kitty informs Wolverine that Ogun, who can now possess the body of a corpse, is back to plague them.

Rigby brings the computers back on line to purge Ogun from the memory, but then becomes possessed by the ninja's spirit.
name: The Mission

description: Hoping to finally discover the source of his inhuman abilities, Mitch tries to assemble a strike team that can lead him to the lab where he was originally resurrected. Meanwhile, his darling wife puts a contract out on her husband--and who should answer it but the Hitman, Tommy Monaghan?
name: Dead Reckoning

description: The Creeper is out and causing havoc.  Punks on the street need to beware.  Jack Boyd finds himself in the apartment of Vera Sweet and not getting the warmest of welcomes.
name: Shadow in the Mirror

description: After finding out how much his trust fund was worth, Dick decided it was time to get a car. He rented out an old showroom to do his thing. He built the vehicle so that he could interchange the body when needed. He took it out for a test drive, not knowing a man-bat was watching from above.
name: Wheels

description: Heroes Return. The Fantastic Four head to Paris to take on the Ruined, a pan-dimensional race determined to transform reality in the 44-page "Vive la Fantastique!" Mole Man cameo.
name: Vive le Fantastique!

description:
General Notes

Like the previous issues, the title of this one represents a figure of from the mythologies of the Voodoo religion, in this case Baron Samedi although he is only referred to as Baron or Saturday (Samedi is French for Saturday) although his role as the spirit of the dead is explicitly shown in this issue.
name: Samedi

description: Woody's dying and his not-so-pretty life is flashing before his eyes. Quantum has brought him to Galloway & Galloway to see if they can save his life. This of course attracts the attention of our favorite kids with attitude... the Troublemakers! Can Zeus: Control save Woody? Will the kids stop harassing Quantum about his cape?
name: Capes

description: Sam and Twitch discover the remains of Spawn. When they try to remove the body, they find themselves between warring alley gangs. The Freak takes Twitch hostage, while Spawn recovers
name: Freaky

description: Claudine's dead and someone's stolen Josey's head, and things are looking rough with Nettie on the domestic front. As if that isn't enough it turns out Shadowman has the stone killers of the TonTon Macoute on his tail.
name: Clear Blue Skies, Part 2
The Spook

description: John Irons has been using his responsibilities as Steel to help hide his feelings for Amanda Quick, but he's about to realize that all the armor in the world can't protect him from his true feelings. Meanwhile, John's niece Natasha goes home for the holidays, but is discouraged to learn that home isn't as she remembers.
name: The Message

description: Asteroid A-271 is plummeting towards Earth, and President Eisenhower has made a personal plea for Doctor Tomorrow to itnervene. But Tomorrow smells a set-up. Using his incredible future technology he breaks into the top secret computer databases of the fifties. But here he'll find more than just files and tape-drives. He runs smack into the most dangerous person he will ever meet - a twelve year-old Native American from the future named Mushroom Cloud!
name: All the Way to the End!

description:
The brief life of Ninjak has led to this moment! Now he faces Masterlord Akuma - the being he was created to destroy. Hanging in the balance is the life of the man who would just as soon see Ninjak rotting in prison! All plotlines are sewn up in this conclusion and Denny Meechum will not leave this issue unscathed!

Final issue.

name: Out of the Cage: Hell: Canto XIII

volume.name: Solar, Man Of The Atom: Hell On Earth

description: The alien creators of the X-O armor have come to claim the armor...and the Earth along with it! Can Donovan Wylie withstand an army of aliens bearing armor identical to his own?
name: Reunion

description: OverviewA daring infiltration into the enemy's camp turns sour as Tarzan is captured, but Korak himself catches the daughter of Jemadar Ortiz, and she may provide the key . . . both to Tarzan's rescue, and to the defeat of the lunar invaders!
name: Tarzan vs. The Moon Men (Part 3 of 4)

description: Lord Noriyuki and Tomoe escape the traitor in their ranks but are on the run from assassins of the Conspiracy of Eight. Meanwhile, Gen has a choice to make: to go after the injured Inazuma for her reward or search for Usagi, who is being pursued by a band of killers? Usagi realizes that he, indeed, is carrying Grasscutter, the sword of the gods. Should he deliver it to the Shogun or to its rightful owner, the Emperor, possibly starting a civil war?
name: Grasscutter, Chapter 4: Noriyuki and Tomoe

description: Dick Grayson and Bruce continue arguing even after Dick's college graduation. After a battle with the Joker with Batman and Batgirl, Dick finds himself being forced to save Barbara. After the fight, Dick is so angry he punches Batman, and decides to leave Gotham despite the protsts of Alfred and Barbara.
name: Book Two: Graduation Day

volume.name: The Batman Adventures: The Lost Years

description: The Spook, a former special operative for the U.S. government and now apparently a real spook, dies at the hands of someone else at the mansion. Consumed by vengeance, the Spook plans on killing everyone else in the mansion, one by one, to find his murderer. "Spook" part 2.
name: Spook: Two of Three

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description: Spotlighting Challenger Marlon Corbett, this issue explores the mythical banshee, a spirit that predicts death.  When a Banshee predicts the death of an unborn child, will Marlon have to make the ultimate sacrifice?

Cameron Chase is late for her first day of work at the Department of Extranormal Operations. Anything involving meta-humans comes under their jurisdiction, including a youngster in Ohio who has starting throwing fire. Chase is immediately sent to Ohio, along with the head of field personnel Sandy Barrett, to find the person who has started burning things. They find him and convince him to volunteer for training to control his powers, but things don't always go the way they want.
name: Baptized In Fire

description: Filling in for Wally while he recuperates from the injuries he suffered in the battle with The Suit, Jay Garrick spends a typical day in Keystone City, lunching with friends, battling super-villains, keeping a date with his wife for their anniversary... and fighting the clock to save the life of an old foe turned friend.
name: Still Life in the Fast Lane

description:
A new story arc begins with "Who Dares Wins" Part 1. The past comes back to haunt Tommy Monaghan and Natt after a group of S.A.S soldiers are sent to kill the duo as revenge for a "friendly fire" incident during Desert Storm.

A long time ago, a horrible mistake happened in the Iraqi desert. Now the consequences have come home for Tommy and Nat, in the form of British SAS assassins.
name: Who Dares Wins, Part One

description: Part 1 of the 2-part "Devonian Age"! A well-intentioned man wants to rule the world and sets an elaborate trap that will use Impulse's super-speed to power a time machine allowing him to seize control in the past. But, as a side effect, the scheme traps Impulse and Max in prehistoric times, where anything they do -- even eating dinner -- could have horrible consequences for the present. Note: This month, Impulse also appears in IMPULSE/ATOM DOUBLE-SHOT #1.  ...
name: The Devonian Age

description: The 30th Century heroine Inferno concludes her first solo adventure! For your average teenage girl, staying up all night locked in North America's largest shopping mall might be some form of nirvana. But for a time-lost youth from the 30th Century, one with a profound fear of the dark, the experience may be a little less than perfect -- especially when the girl in question is pursued by a demon fueled by her own fears! Inferno's got just 8 hours to defeat her demons (both physical and psychological) if she ever wants to return to the light again.
name: Who By Fire

description:
Solicitation

The exciting three-issue miniseries teaming the JLA with the fallen angel Zauriel (first seen in JLA #6-7) continues, as the Martian Manhunter lays dying! While the JLA rushes to the aid of their fallen comrade, the fallen angel Zauriel must flee the allied forces of Heaven and Hell with Shannon, his one true love. But when the Father of Lies, Neron, gets together with Asmodel, the Lord Angel of the Bull Host, there's very little that can stand in their way, and Zauriel may have to make the ultimate sacrifice to save his beloved.  
 

Plot

Shannon Coyne tells her boyfriend, male nurse Jerry, that her guardian angel Zauriel has approached her and professed his love. After Etrigan’s attack last issue, Zauriel wants them to flee to Los Angeles, and Shannon needs Jerry to come with them for support. They drive from San Francisco to L.A., with Zauriel watching from the skies.
 
At the Watchtower, Superman has discovered Martian Manhunter’s dying body, and the Justice League try to resuscitate him. While Batman and Aztek try to help Manhunter, the rest of the League scour San Francisco for either Asmodel (the cause of Martian Manhunter’s condition) or Zauriel (Asmodel’s arch-enemy who has not responded to the JLA’s call).
 
In Los Angeles, Zauriel, Shannon and Jerry seek the protection of Michael, another angel that renounced his place in heaven to become mortal. When Michael realizes that Asmodel is involved, he refuses. When Michael tries to talk Zauriel from throwing away his life for Shannon, Asmodel attacks. Asmodel and Zauriel fight in the air above Los Angeles, and Zauriel destroys Asmodel’s flesh suit with his sonic scream. Realizing that he must stop Asmodel and Neron’s scheme to assault heaven, Zauriel has Michael kill him, returning Zauriel to heaven.
 
At the Watchtower, Martian Manhunter has died from his wounds, only to find himself standing before the gates of heaven, watching it come under siege from Neron’s demons.
name: The Damnation Game

description: Part 2 of the four-part "Lightning & Stars," continued from STARMAN #39 (also released this week)! Bulletman, branded a traitor by the media, escapes from jail and heads for Opal City -- home of the only man who can clear his name: the original Starman! Sarge Steel asks Captain Marvel to find Bulletman and bring him back -- dead or alive! Continued in STARMAN #40. ...
name: Lightning and Stars Part Two Bite The Bullet!

description:
Beginning a story that will change PREACHER forever. Our heroes go to Monument Valley, where Jesse plans his showdown with God. But Starr and the Saint of Killers have other plans for Jesse's future. ...

Jesse, Tulip and Cassidy head out to Monument Valley to prepare to tap the wisdom of the Natives - through peyote; Starr brings The Grail to bear and gathers his strength.
name: Once Upon A Time (War in the Sun Part 1)

description: An extra-sized issue launches a 3-part European adventure, featuring Lady Shiva and King Snake! Distraught over recent events, Tim Drake leaves Gotham behind, embarking on a European journey to clear his mind and continue the martial-arts training he began years ago. Drawn to a mysterious girl who needs his help, Tim is unaware that his old enemy, King Snake has hired Lady Shiva to kill not only the girl, but anyone who tries to help her. ...
name: Faster, Faster!

description: In his everyday persona as the Reverend Hawsley, the Cannon cuts a high-profile deal within a gold-fencing ring--a development unknown to the Sandman as he joins the Cannon's nighttime investigation of a freighter with a remarkable cargo.
name: The Cannon Act III of IV

description: Under the suggestion of Father Craemer, Corrigan decides to leave the mantle of the Spectre and give his soul the rest it always needed. As Craemer prepares Corrigan's last rites, Corrigan finds out that his burial will be anything but lonely...
name: Final Rites

description: Part 1 of the four-part "Lightning & Stars" crossover with THE POWER OF SHAZAM! Bulletman, Golden Age hero of World War II, is revealed to have been a Nazi collaborator! As a manhunt ensues, Bulletman flees Fawcett City, seeking aid from one of the few men he can trust: Ted Knight, the original Starman. Ted enlists his son Jack's aid to help hide Bulletman and all seems to be going well... until Captain Marvel finds Jack. Note: "Lightning & Stars" continues in THE POWER OF SHAZAM! #35, also offered this week. ...
name: Lightning and Stars, Part One

deck: Supergirl gets her wings (and some handy flaming eye beams to zap bad people with) in a fight with Despero. God has a talk with Linda's father while her mother is in the hospital.
description:
Supergirl, in her altered form, defeats Despero.

Supergirl vs. Despero, part 2.
name: Divine Inspiration

description: Clark Kent is Superman... isn't he? Even Clark's not too sure anymore when he actually meets the Man of Steel on several occasions! Has Clark lost his mind, or is this all part of a bigger mystery? This issue's cover features an actual background from the Superman animated series on the Kids WB!.
name: Clark Kent, You're A Nobody!

description: In a self-contained story, crusading journalist Spider Jerusalem is thrust into the world of bizarre religious movements that have sprung up during his five-year absence from The City.  But Spider's bad attitude makes him an unlikely convert, even to the most fervent evangelists alive.
name: God Riding Shotgun

description: Queen Hippolyta has taken up the mantle of Wonder Woman…and Jay Garrick, the Golden Age Flash, realizes he has seen her in that capacity in the past. In the 1940s, to be precise, where he suddenly remembers her fighting alongside the Justice Society of America. So together, Flash and Wonder Woman travel back in time to discover the cause of the paradox…and encounter the JSA.
name: Unfamiliar Friends

description:
Captain America must battle Hydra in order to prevent them from releasing a computer virus on a US Navy fleet. In the process, he loses one of his greatest assets- his shield!

Terrorist forces take over a United States Navy submarine. Naturally they do not last long as Cap and the sailors put a beating on the bad guys. Unfortunately, in the chaos Cap loses his shield to the depths of the ocean in order to save an innocent life. Though he sees it as no choice at all, it still will come to hurt.
name: To Serve and Protect

description: With Danny leaving the H4H, the rest of the team meets at Oracle Inc. to greet their new lawyer - the Incredible She-Hulk!
name: Revelations (Book One)

description: Parnival Plunder's plan has a secret backer, the mad god Thanos.
name: Urban Jungle (Chapter Three): Outgrowth

description: The ever-restless Quicksilver can’t seem to keep calm while visiting New Attilan, home world of the Inhumans. What is the source of Quicksilver’s restlessness? Guest-starring the Inhuman Royal Family and the villainy of Maximus the Mad!
name: The Inhuman Race
A Christmas Story

description: Spider-Man is framed for murder when a body is found hanging outside the police station in webbing.  Just when Peter thinks the situation couldn't get any worse, the Green Goblin begins to stalk him.  Now uncertain and slowly becoming more erratic, Peter beings to question if Norman Osborn is really behind it all.
name: Who Did Joey Z?
Nobody Knows the Tribbles I've Seen

description: Mia Colt goes into the future and her mere disappearance completely changes the Star Trek world. James Kirk and Montgomery Scott are cargo shippers and Christopher Pike is still in good health and Captain of the Enterprise A. Kirk finds Mia and is determined to get her back into her own timeline. This requires him going into Klingon territory and runs up against Captain Change and Captain Pike and it is hard to tell between the two.who dislikes Kirk more.
name: Future Tense (Part Two)

description: On their way back to the Alpha Quadrant, the U.S.S. Voyager provides what they think will be routine aid to a disabled ship.
name: Survival Of The Fittest, Part One

description:
Zemo unveils his plan for world domination -- but which of the Thunderbolts will side with him?

Zemo's plan of world domination appears to be a success, but the Thunderbolts don't like it. The Thunderbolts plan against Zemo, and, in the end, are able to summon the Earth's Mightiest Heroes, the Avengers! But when the Avengers arrive, Zemo reveals that he has control over their minds as well, and orders the Avengers to attack the Thunderbolts! What will happen next?
name: The High Ground

description:
Mayday Parker, the daughter of Peter Parker, is forced to adopt the mantle of her father when the new Green Goblin puts her family in danger.

Note: This issue features the very first appearance of Spider-Girl, the daughter of Spider-Man!
name: LEGACY... IN BLACK AND WHITE
The Greatest Heroes of All Time!

volume.name: Corto Maltese: Ballad of the Salt Sea

description:
Gax gets his own tale when Akiko leads the group to a special place and our little robot friend gets to tell the tale of his Tour of Duty on Fognon-6. 
 
 
It is a tale of peril and danger where the smaller robots have to contend with a harsh senior robot who isnt afraid to punish smaller robots who don't do what they are told to.
An experimental storytelling technique features several one-page tales interspersed with the story of the Norse gods trapping Fenrir the Wolf.
name: The Book of Law, Epilogue: Plyck

description: Daredevil’s looking for answers about Mr. Fear’s riot at Ryker’s Island. When his hunt takes him to a warden’s house, another vigilante’s already inside! Ghost Rider is on the case, and blames Daredevil for the renewed evil in New York City. A motorcycle race ensues to catch a corrupt warden!
name: Devil And The Demon

description: Woody and Quantum have switched bodies, and let me tell you... it's ugly.
name: Switch

description: The prequel to "Days of Future Past" concludes! With the Council of the Chosen's apocalyptic plan to create planet-wide cataclysms about to come to fruition, and Helmut Zemo, the power-mongering leader of the Sentinels' Human High Council, hunting him, Wolverine must join forces with the man who irrevocably wrecked his life!
name: Chain Reactions

description: The 12-issue maxi-series revealing the earliest adventures of the World's Greatest Heroes continues! A team of super-villains, all under the command of the immortal Vandal Savage, vow to destroy the new Justice League of America (Aquaman, Black Canary, Flash Barry Allen, Green Lantern Hal Jordan, and J'onn J'onzz) even before Earth's five newest heroes can establish themselves as a team to be reckoned with. Plus: What is Batman's connection to the recently formed Justice League?
name: Group Dynamic
Bury My Heart at the Bottle City of Love
The Replacement God

description: Sam, Twitch and Spawn struggle to stop the slaughter in the alley, but Spawn becomes powerless in an area called the "dead zone". Spawn tracks down the Freak and drowns him in his worms and insects
name: Darkness

description:
Xena and Gabrielle on their way to the wedding of King Gregor and Pandora, stumble upon a woman being attacked by "Thanatos", a minion of "Hades" sent to collect the souls of the dead. The women, tells Xena, that she is Cassandra of Troy, blessed by the god "Apollo" himself, with the gift of seeing the future and warns Xena of her untimely death at the hands of a mysterious woman known only as Callisto.

A hideous Hydra controlled by Callisto soon attacks the guests at the wedding - Can Xena and Gabrielle save the day once more? or will Cassandra's Prophecy foretelling the death of Xena Come true?
name: Xena: Warrior Princess vs Callisto

description: Guest-starring the Sovereign Seven's Power Girl!  Maxima decides that Aquaman is her perfect mate, and whatever Maxima wants, Maxima gets.  So she captures the Sea King, and only Dolphin, Deep Blue, Tsunami, and guest-star Power Girl can save him.
name: Babewatch

description:
In this issue, we start out with Lex Luthor trying to make another appeal to Aztek, to have him join the Injustice League. We then cut to Batman, who reiterates that there are three people within the Injustice League who is working for him.

Before Batman Superman and the Martian Manhunter are able to reach the Satellite, the Injustice League discovers that Plastic Man has been diguised as the Joker. When they do arrive, Mirror Master walks off, having been paid off by Batman, and the Green Arrow turns his Bow and Arrow on Lex Luthor.

Plastic Man tries to surround Circe, but she calls him, and then turns him into a pig. Doctor Polaris changes the light in the Base, and even takes control of Supermans body. After a short fight the Justice League wins and has the Philosophers Stone, as well as disarming the nuclear weapons in the Watchtower. Unfortunately, the Joker comes in and causes a little chaos,.
name: Rock of Ages, Part 6: Stone of Destiny

description:
John's American holiday takes a nasty turn when the First of the Fallen unveils his latest scheme; and, back home in London, John's past catches up with him. "Up the Down Staircase" part 2.

An old enemy of John's is using the unique lifestyles of Americans to sow madness.
name: Up The Down Staircase, Part 2

description: Deadpool has just had the greatest night of his life. He spent the night with the woman he loves but something is very wrong. It sends him off the edge and he comes home to find Weasel in his hideout. But nothing is ever that easy in the life of the Merc with a Mouth: this was all on top of T-Ray's challenge, which, ultimately leads to terrible consequences.
name: The Drowning Man Part 2 or I Left My Life in San Francisco

description: Guest-starring Ragman! A rash of hate crimes breaks out in the ghettos of Gotham City, and it looks like Ragman is the culprit. It's up to Batman to determine his old ally's innocence... or guilt.
name: Suit of Evil Souls

description: The Societe lays a trap for Shadowman at the birthday bash for Judge Napoleon. If Mike manages to survive this deadly celebration he'll have a chance to rock the voodoo underground of New Orleans to its very core.
name: The Hoodoo Bash, Part 1

description:
While aboard a flight to Alaska, Scott and Jean are attacked by agents of A.I.M.!

During a flight to Alaska, Jean Grey tries to psychically pinpoint the location of Charles Xavier, but fails when she feels another presence probe her mind and she discusses it with Scott Summers. Soon, another passenger begins raving about somebody else being is his mind, and the flight attendants arrange to get him a sedative.

At the Xavier Institute, the X-Men are cleaning up debris from the latest mess, as Archangel arrives, too late to see Scott and Jean off. He receives a very cool welcome from his teammates who feel he's not making an effort to be an X-Man, so he departs. Later, Sam Guthrie receives a letter from Tabitha Smith, and decides to join her at the "Colossal Man" gathering in Texas.

Back in the skies above Canada, Jean gets up to find Scott some aspirin to ease the pain of his recent surgery. Unexpectedly, A. I. M. agents board their aircraft and locate Dr. Sibelius, a scientist who has tried to elude them. They demand from him the location of "the entity", but they stun him when he refuses to cooperate. The entity then begins to probe the minds of those aboard, and they are forced to recall traumatic memories.

Jean enters the cargo hold to find the "entity", and locates it in an armored container set to explode if tampered with. Mentally, she communicates with it, learning it has been held captive and tortured by A. I. M. scientists. She has to hide when the A. I. M. agents escort Sibelius' companions into the hold to find the "entity". Again, the "entity" invades the minds of all aboard, and the plane's wing collides with the A. I. M. cratf which plummets to its doom. In the confusion, Scott tackles the agent guarding the cockpit, while below, Jean decks the one agent left standing. She again reaches out to the "entity", and begs it to calm the crew and passengers so the plane may land safely, and it complies.

The aircraft comes to an emergency landing in Manitoba, and Department H agents take the container holding the "entity" into their custody.
name: In Sin Air

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: Weatherman learns that there are two operatives in the field that Stormwatch has no idea about. The two operatives, Midnighter and Apollo, worked for Henry Bendix and were his very secret branch of Stormwatch. Weatherman decides to send a crew to contact and retrieve them.
name: A Finer World: Part 1

description:
PKNA #14

Carpe diem / Carpe Diem
name: Carpe diem

description: Luse is captured by the Blood Guard and is being questioned. Jace decides its time for them to leave.

description:
Legendary artist Jim Starlin guest-pencils a spacefaring issue of GREEN LANTERN! Kyle travels into deep space to answer a distress call, and finds its source: a floating city where robots do all the work. Corpulent overlords are disappearing, and it's at the hands of a foe that Kyle thinks may be in the right.

The story starts with our hero the whimsical Kyle Rayner blasting off to a far away planet filled with robots. Once there he is escorted to the "leader" of the place and reminisces about why the hell he's here. Turn out the pricks sent for him and demanded he come because it was his "job" as a gl to protect the universe. They even called him away from his work, you know art work! he is after all a struggling artist at this point. The leader is a "Mojo" looking alien who gives him orders like he's his lap dog. Kyle being the good guy he is goes along to hunt the would be killer of all the organic spineless a$$wipe aliens and runs into a spider creature. Kyle wraps it up and listens to things from his point of view.

The spinless schuck send in his robots to kill the creature after kyle decides against it. They tussle and kyle comes out the victor and since the spineless nit wit sent all his robots against kyle, they have no more robots left. Kyle then reveals that the spider alien was simply feeding her young and ment no ill will toward them. Spinless goes mad demanding their death. Kyle swoops them up to crry back to there planet and leav spinless to fend for himself on his barren robotless planet.
name: Servants & Masters

description: After heading into a trap, Boy and her brother battle the Invisibles' arch nemeses at a secret death camp in the American heartland. But even the Invisibles are not enough to thwart the deviant plans of the New World Order. All the mysteries surrounding the Hand of Glory are revealed here!
name: American Death Camp, Part Three: Counting to Ten

description: Part 1 of  the 6-part "Slave of Heavens." Tim has released his power into the world with hopes of making it a better place for everyone to live -- but when he learns that the magic he's given up has been stolen by the same changeling who has stolen his face, his past, and his family, he returns to London to confront the thief. Unfortunately, that thief is now quite possibly the most powerful magician of the age, and he would like nothing better than to see Tim dead.
name: Slave of Heavens, Part 1: The Veil

description:
Aboard the SHIELD Helicarrier, Kitty Pryde resists a romantic advance by her ally, Rigby Fallon, who she soon learns is possessed by the spirit of her ninja enemy, Ogun. Ogun once again infects the aircraft's computers, throwing the ship careening out of control through New York City.

To get Ogun to leave Rigby's body, she challenges him to a duel on the astral plane; Ogun accepts. As they battle, Ogun sends the Helicarrier on a collision course with the Statue of Liberty. Wolverine hauls a missile to the computer banks, to destroy the vault door barring his way to the computer shut-off panel. They blow the door, and Wolverine shreds the computer, returning manual control to Dum Dum Dugan at the helm.

Meanwhile, Kitty has realized she can overwhelm Ogun, who has possessed a corpse, with the power of her own lifeforce. Ogun ceases fighting, regretting what he has become, and reliquishes control of the Helicarrier.
name: Pryde Goeth Before The Fall
